1 A BILL FOR AN ACT relating to appropriations; to amend Laws 2025, LB261,
2 section 88; Laws 2025, LB261, sections 69, 100, 164, 246, 279, 280,
3 285, and 300, as amended by sections 59, 75, 99, 119, 125, 126, 127,
4 and 128, respectively, Legislative Bill 1071, One Hundred Ninth
5 Legislature, Second Session, 2026; and section 81, Legislative Bill
6 1072, One Hundred Ninth Legislature, Second Session, 2026; to define
7 terms; to provide and change appropriations for purposes of carrying
8 out legislation enacted by the One Hundred Ninth Legislature, Second
9 Session, 2026; to change provisions relating to appropriations and a
10 transfer of funds; to repeal the original sections; and to declare
11 an emergency.
12 Be it enacted by the people of the State of Nebraska,
-1-

LB1209 LB1209
2026 2026
1 Section 1. DEFINITION OF APPROPRIATION PERIOD.
2 For purposes of this act and any other legislative bill passed by
3 the One Hundred Ninth Legislature, First or Second Session, which
4 appropriates funds, FY2025-26 means the period July 1, 2025, through June
5 30, 2026; FY2026-27 means the period July 1, 2026, through June 30, 2027;
6 FY2027-28 means the period July 1, 2027, through June 30, 2028; and
7 FY2028-29 means the period July 1, 2028, through June 30, 2029.
8 Sec. 2. APPROPRIATION LANGUAGE.
9 There are hereby appropriated, for FY2025-26 and FY2026-27, the sums
10 set forth in this act to each agency for each program from the respective
11 funds for the general operations of state government, postsecondary
12 education, and state aid, except as otherwise appropriated.
13 Sec. 3. UNEXPENDED BALANCES AND CERTIFIED ENCUMBRANCES.
14 All General Fund appropriations existing on June 30, 2025, in excess
15 of expended and certified encumbrance amounts are hereby lapsed unless
16 otherwise provided. All Cash Fund and Revolving Fund appropriations
17 existing on June 30, 2025, in excess of expended and certified
18 encumbrance amounts are hereby lapsed unless otherwise expressly
19 provided. All certified encumbrance amounts on June 30, 2025, and June
20 30, 2026, are hereby reappropriated for FY2025-26 and FY2026-27,
21 respectively, which amounts shall be in addition to the amounts shown in
22 this act.
23 Sec. 4. REAPPROPRIATION OF BALANCE, FY2025-26 to FY2026-27.
24 In addition to the appropriations set forth in this act, there are
25 hereby reappropriated all unexpended appropriation balances existing on
26 June 30, 2026, for FY2026-27, to the respective agencies, programs, and
27 funds listed in this act, except as otherwise provided in this act.
28 Sec. 5. There are hereby reappropriated for each agency, program,
29 and fund for FY2025-26 and FY2026-27, any appropriation by the One
30 Hundred Seventh Legislature, First or Second Session, of the unexpended
31 and unencumbered appropriation balances of the Federal Funds allocated to
-2-

LB1209 LB1209
2026 2026
1 the State of Nebraska from the federal Coronavirus State Fiscal Recovery
2 Fund pursuant to the federal American Rescue Plan Act of 2021, 42 U.S.C.
3 802, as amended, unless otherwise indicated in this act and any other
4 legislative bill passed by the One Hundred Eighth Legislature, First or
5 Second Session. Such reappropriation shall retain any provided
6 limitations established by the appropriating legislative bill unless
7 otherwise indicated within this act and any other legislative bill passed
8 by the One Hundred Eighth Legislature, First or Second Session.
9 Sec. 6. NEBRASKA ACCOUNTING SYSTEM MANUAL DEFINITIONS.
10 The definitions contained in the Nebraska Accounting System Manual,
11 and any amendments thereto, on file with the Clerk of the Legislature,
12 are hereby adopted by the Legislature as the definitions for this act,
13 except as provided in section 7 of this act.
14 Sec. 7. LIMITATION ON SALARIES, WAGES, AND PER DIEMS.
15 (1) For purposes of this act, (a) SALARY LIMIT shall mean total
16 expenditures for permanent and temporary salaries and per diems and (b)
17 total expenditures for permanent and temporary salaries and per diems
18 shall mean all remuneration paid to employees treated as taxable
19 compensation by the Internal Revenue Service or subject to social
20 security coverage, specifically including payments accounted for as
21 vacation, holidays, sick leave, military leave, funeral leave, maternity
22 leave, administrative leave, compensatory time, deferred compensation, or
23 any other similar form, and amounts withheld pursuant to law, but
24 excluding state contributions for social security, retirement, and
25 employee insurance plans.
26 (2) Total expenditures for permanent and temporary salaries and per
27 diems shall be limited to the amount shown except when federal funds in
28 excess of the amount shown are available and approved by the Governor.
29 Expenditures for permanent and temporary salaries and per diems from such
30 grants shall be in addition to the limitation on permanent and temporary
31 salaries and per diems otherwise shown in this act. No agency shall
-3-

LB1209 LB1209
2026 2026
1 request any state funds for continuation or replacement of any such
2 personnel or activities in future budget requests. To the extent
3 feasible, requests for increases in the limitation on permanent and
4 temporary salaries and per diems shall be addressed to the Appropriations
5 Committee of the Legislature when the Legislature is in session.
6 (3) Expenditures for permanent and temporary salaries resulting from
7 awards made to employees under sections 81-1346 to 81-1354 shall be in
8 addition to the limitations on permanent and temporary salaries and per
9 diems otherwise shown in this act.
10 (4) The limitation on expenditures for permanent and temporary
11 salaries and per diems for FY2026-27 as enumerated in this act shall be
12 the basis for continuation funding for each fiscal year of the succeeding
13 biennium.
14 (5) The limitation on expenditures for permanent and temporary
15 salaries and per diems for FY2025-26 shall be increased by certified
16 encumbrance amounts from FY2024-25 for permanent and temporary salaries
17 and per diems. The limitation on expenditures for permanent and temporary
18 salaries and per diems for FY2026-27 shall be increased by certified
19 encumbrance amounts from FY2025-26 for permanent and temporary salaries
20 and per diems. Encumbered amounts shall be calculated in accordance with
21 section 81-138.01.
22 (6) The limitation on expenditures for permanent and temporary
23 salaries and per diems shall only apply to remuneration paid to state
24 employees or per diem payments made to members of state boards or
25 commissions.
26 (7) The budget administrator of the budget division of the
27 Department of Administrative Services may administratively increase the
28 limitation on expenditures for permanent and temporary salaries and per
29 diems upon receipt of a request for such increase from the director of a
30 state agency certifying the actual amount of the payment to a former
31 employee of such agency, or such employee's beneficiary upon the death of
-4-

LB1209 LB1209
2026 2026
1 the employee, of accumulated vacation and sick leave pursuant to section
2 81-1325 and the rules and regulations of the State Personnel System
3 governing such payments.
4 Sec. 8. DRAWING AND PAYING WARRANTS.
5 The Director of Administrative Services shall draw warrants upon the
6 proper fund in the state treasury for an amount not to exceed the
7 appropriations set forth in this act upon presentation of proper
8 documentation. The State Treasurer shall pay the warrants out of the
9 appropriate funds.
